-spinoff-plans-timeline-hbo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BGame%20of%20Thrones%26quot%3B%20spinoff%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20based%20on%20George%20R.%20R.%20Martin's%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20fictional%20history%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-of-the-dragon-targaryen-kid-guide-photos-jace-aegon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHouse%20Targaryen%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20book%20is%20written%20as%20an%20overview%20of%20major%20events%20during%20the%20dynasty's%20reign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Martin's%20main%20series%20(%26quot%3BA%20Song%20of%20Ice%20and%20Fire%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20inspired%20%26quot%3BGame%20of%20Thrones%26quot%3B)%2C%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20told%20from%20the%20major%20characters'%20points%20of%20view%20but%20is%20recounted%20in%20retrospect%20by%20maesters%2C%20members%20of%20the%20royal%20court%2C%20and%20other%20third-party%20observers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%26quot%3B%20readers%20don't%20get%20definitive%20causes%20or%20clear%20motivations%20for%20why%20characters%20take%20certain%20actions%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20book%20may%20be%20missing%20key%20in-universe%20information.%20As%20the%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%26quot%3B%20narrator%20frequently%20notes%2C%20not%20even%20eyewitness%20accounts%20are%20entirely%20reliable.%20His%20sources%20often%20disagree%2C%20each%20saddled%20with%20unique%20baggage%2C%20blind%20spots%2C%20and%20biases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20TV%20writers%20hired%20for%20HBO's%20adaptation%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-of-the-dragon-asoiaf-prophecy-reveal-came-from-george-rr-martin-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleeway%20with%20the%20story%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20opportunity%20to%20create%20a%20consistent%20canon%20of%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20let's%20take%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20some%20of%20the%20pivotal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-of-the-dragon-saddest-deaths-ranked%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20far%2C%20and%20how%20they%20compare%20to%20the%20details%20found%20in%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAemma's%20final%20moments%20of%20life%20are%20made%20more%20brutal%20by%20Viserys%20opting%20for%20a%20C-section.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Paddy%20Considine%20and%20Sian%20Brooke%20as%20King%20Viserys%20and%20Queen%20Aemma%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20season%20one.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62ffafccf1df7e0018eb59fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPaddy%20Considine%20and%20Sian%20Brooke%20as%20King%20Viserys%20and%20Queen%20Aemma%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20season%20one.%3Cp%3EOllie%20Upton%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20show%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EDirector%20Miguel%20Sapochnik%20says%20the%20scene%20that%20killed%20Queen%20Aemma%20(Sian%20Brooke)%20was%20designed%20to%20show%20how%20King%20Viserys%20(Paddy%20Considine)%20%26quot%3Beffectively%20murdered%26quot%3B%20his%20beloved%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Aemma%20goes%20into%20labor%2C%20her%20baby%20is%20facing%20the%20wrong%20direction%2C%20and%20the%20maesters%20can't%20get%20it%20to%20turn.%20This%20means%20Aemma%20will%20certainly%20die%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20small%20chance%20they%20can%20save%20the%20baby%20by%20cutting%20it%20out%20of%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20maester%20offers%20the%20choice%20to%20Viserys%2C%20who%20picks%20the%20surgery%20without%20consulting%20Aemma%20or%20telling%20her%20what's%20about%20to%20happen.%20Instead%2C%20she's%20dragged%20down%20on%20the%20bed%20and%20restrained%20while%20the%20maester%20cuts%20open%20her%20belly.%20She%20bleeds%20to%20death%20as%20the%20baby%20is%20%26quot%3Bborn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20book%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EDeath%20by%20childbirth%20is%20fairly%20commonplace%20in%20Westeros%2C%20and%20it's%20treated%20as%20such%20in%20the%20text.%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%26quot%3B%20provides%20no%20details%20or%20context%20to%20Aemma's%20death%2C%20and%20doesn't%20mention%20Viserys%20being%20a%20part%20of%20the%20labor%20and%20delivery%20process%20at%20all%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BQueen%20Aemma%20was%20brought%20to%20bed%20in%20Maegor's%20Holdfast%20and%20died%20whilst%20giving%20birth%20to%20the%20son%20that%20Viserys%20Targaryen%20had%20desired%20for%20so%20long.%20The%20boy%20(named%20Baelon%2C%20after%20the%20king's%20father)%20survived%20her%20only%20by%20a%20day%2C%20leaving%20king%20and%20court%20bereft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERhea's%20death%20in%20the%20book%20is%20regarded%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bhunting%20accident%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20cold-blooded%20murder.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221650%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20scene%20from%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%2C%26quot%3B%20season%20one%20episode%20five%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20Light%20the%20Way.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6327d282edbe7f00190ebd21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221238%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaemon%20and%20Rhea%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20show%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20season%20one%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-daemon-targaryen-die-house-of-the-dragon-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrince%20Daemon%20Targaryen%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(Matt%20Smith)%20is%20married%20to%20Lady%20Rhea%20Royce%20(Rachel%20Redford)%2C%20though%20neither%20is%20particularly%20happy%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoping%20to%20marry%20his%20royal%20niece%20instead%2C%20Daemon%20sneaks%20up%20on%20Rhea%20during%20a%20hunting%20trip%20and%20spooks%20her%20horse.%20After%20she's%20thrown%2C%20Rhea%20is%20paralyzed%20from%20the%20neck%20down%20and%20unable%20to%20fight%20back.%20She%20lobs%20insults%20at%20Daemon%20until%20he%20picks%20up%20a%20rock%20and%20bashes%20in%20her%20skull.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20book%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAccording%20to%20the%20historical%20record%2C%20Rhea's%20death%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20tragic%20mishap.%26quot%3B%20Daemon%20is%20not%20suspected%20of%20being%20involved%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BThe%20'bronze%20bitch'%20of%20Runestone%2C%20Lady%20Rhea%20Royce%2C%20fell%20from%20her%20horse%20whilst%20hawking%20and%20cracked%20her%20skull%20upon%20a%20stone.%20She%20lingered%20for%20nine%20days%20before%20finally%20feeling%20well%20enough%20to%20leave%20her%20bed%E2%80%A6only%20to%20collapse%20and%20die%20within%20an%20hour%20of%20rising.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJoffrey%20is%20killed%20by%20Criston%20in%20both%20the%20show%20and%20the%20book%2C%20but%20in%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20death%20happens%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20a%20tourney.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Solly%20McLeod%20and%20Fabien%20Frankel%20as%20Joffrey%20Lonmouth%20and%20Criston%20Cole%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20season%20one.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63364cf625c9a90018a638f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESolly%20McLeod%20and%20Fabien%20Frankel%20as%20Joffrey%20Lonmouth%20and%20Criston%20Cole%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20season%20one.%3Cp%3EHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20show%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20still%20teenagers%2C%20Lord%20Laenor%20Velaryon%20(Theo%20Nate)%20and%20Princess%20Rhaenyra%20Targaryen%20(Milly%20Alcock)%20agree%20to%20get%20married%20%E2%80%94%20not%20out%20of%20love%2C%20but%20duty%20to%20their%20families.%20They%20also%20secretly%20agree%20to%20keep%20their%20marriage%20open%2C%20since%20Laenor%20is%20gay%2C%20and%20Rhaenyra%20is%20having%20an%20affair%20with%20Ser%20Criston%20Cole%20(Fabien%20Frankel).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESer%20Joffrey%20Lonmouth%20(Solly%20McLeod)%2C%20Laenor's%20lover%2C%20outs%20himself%20to%20Criston%20as%20the%20future%20king%20consort's%20boyfriend.%20Big%20mistake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECole%2C%20embarrassed%20and%20infuriated%20by%20the%20exposure%20of%20his%20own%20secret%20tryst%20with%20Rhaenyra%2C%20lashes%20out%20and%20beats%20Joffrey%20to%20death%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20wedding%20welcome%20feast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20book%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%26quot%3B%20historians%20recall%20that%20Joffrey%20was%20killed%20by%20Criston%20during%20a%20tourney%2C%20during%20which%20Criston%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bfighting%20in%20a%20black%20fury%26quot%3B%20against%20all%20his%20opponents.%20Joffrey's%20relationship%20with%20Laenor%20isn't%20mentioned%20as%20a%20possible%20motivation%20for%20his%20death%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BCole's%20favorite%20weapon%20was%20the%20morningstar%2C%20and%20the%20blows%20he%20rained%20down%20on%20Ser%20Laenor's%20champion%20cracked%20his%20helm%20and%20left%20him%20senseless%20in%20the%20mud.%20Borne%20bloody%20from%20the%20field%2C%20Ser%20Joffrey%20died%20without%20recovering%20consciousness%20six%20days%20later.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHarwin%20and%20Lyonel%20canonically%20die%20in%20a%20fire%20at%20Harrenhal%2C%20but%20the%20show%20clarifies%20the%20arsonist.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221030%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20armor%20holding%20a%20baby%20in%20a%20blanket.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F633388fd1d26f60019aa8022%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22772%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERyan%20Corr%20as%20Ser%20Harwin%20%26quot%3BBreakbones%26quot%3B%20Strong%20in%20the%20sixth%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20show%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0House%20Strong%20controls%20Harrenhal%2C%20the%20largest%20castle%20in%20the%20Riverlands.%20It's%20where%20Ser%20Harwin%20Strong%20(Ryan%20Corr)%20and%20his%20father%2C%20Lyonel%20Strong%20(Gavin%20Spokes)%2C%20meet%20their%20doom%20after%20leaving%20King's%20Landing%20in%20season%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20makes%20it%20clear%20who%20to%20blame%3A%20Larys%20Strong%20(Matthew%20Needham)%2C%20a%20sneaky%20man%20who%20wants%20leverage%20on%20Queen%20Alicent%20(Olivia%20Cooke)%2C%20hires%20two%20miscreants%20to%20set%20the%20castle%20ablaze%20in%20one%20of%20the%20show's%20most%20egregious%20acts%20of%20kinslaying.%20As%20an%20added%20bonus%2C%20with%20his%20older%20brother%20and%20father%20both%20dead%2C%20Larys%20inherits%20Harrenhal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20book%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0Harwin%20and%20Lyonel%20are%20indeed%20killed%20in%20a%20mysterious%20fire%20at%20Harrenhal%2C%20but%20Larys%20is%20floated%20as%20just%20one%20of%20several%20suspects%20for%20the%20arson%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BShortly%20after%20their%20arrival%2C%20a%20fire%20broke%20out%20in%20the%20tower%20where%20they%20were%20sleeping%2C%20and%20both%20father%20and%20son%20were%20killed%2C%20along%20with%20three%20of%20their%20retainers%20and%20a%20dozen%20servants.%20The%20cause%20of%20the%20fire%20was%20never%20determined.%20Some%20put%20it%20down%20to%20simple%20mischance%2C%20whilst%20others%20muttered%20that%20Black%20Harren's%20seat%20was%20cursed%20and%20brought%20only%20doom%20to%20any%20man%20who%20held%20it.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EMany%20suspected%20the%20blaze%20was%20set%20intentionally.%20Mushroom%20suggests%20that%20the%20Sea%20Snake%20was%20behind%20it%2C%20as%20an%20act%20of%20vengeance%20against%20the%20man%20who%20had%20cuckolded%20his%20son.%20Septon%20Eustace%2C%20more%20plausibly%2C%20suspects%20Prince%20Daemon%2C%20removing%20a%20rival%20for%20Princess%20Rhaenyra's%20affections.%20Others%20have%20put%20forth%20the%20notion%20that%20Larys%20Clubfoot%20might%20have%20been%20responsible%3B%20with%20his%20father%20and%20elder%20brother%20dead%2C%20Larys%20Strong%20became%20the%20Lord%20of%20Harrenhal.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20most%20disturbing%20possibility%20was%20advanced%20by%20none%20other%20than%20Grand%20Maester%20Mellos%2C%20who%20muses%20that%20the%20king%20himself%20might%20have%20given%20the%20command.%20If%20Viserys%20had%20come%20to%20accept%20that%20the%20rumors%20about%20the%20parentage%20of%20Rhaenyra's%20children%20were%20true%2C%20he%20might%20well%20have%20wished%20to%20remove%20the%20man%20who%20had%20dishonored%20his%20daughter%2C%20lest%20he%20somehow%20reveal%20the%20bastardy%20of%20her%20sons.%20Were%20that%20so%2C%20Lyonel%20Strong's%20death%20was%20an%20unfortunate%20accident%2C%20for%20his%20lordship's%20decision%20to%20see%20his%20son%20back%20to%20Harrenhal%20had%20been%20unforeseen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELike%20Aemma%2C%20Laena's%20cause%20of%20death%20isn't%20detailed%20in%20the%20book%20beyond%20childbirth.%20The%20show%20gives%20her%20a%20fiery%20end.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22matt%20smith%20as%20daemon%20targaryen%2C%20kneeling%20in%20front%20of%20his%20pregnant%20wife%2C%20laena%20targaryen%2C%20played%20by%20nanna%20blondell.%20daemon%20has%20his%20hands%20over%20laena's%20belly%2C%20and%20she's%20looking%20down%20at%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c7d7a764df161125a0ceb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatt%20Smith%20and%20Nanna%20Blondell%20as%20Daemon%20Targaryen%20and%20Laena%20Velaryon%20in%20season%20one%2C%20episode%20six%20of%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EOllie%20Upton%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20show%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EJust%20like%20Aemma%2C%20Lady%20Laena%20Velaryon%20(Nanna%20Blondell)%20is%20unable%20to%20safely%20deliver%20her%20baby.%20A%20medieval%20C-section%20offers%20a%20tiny%20chance%20for%20the%20baby's%20survival%2C%20and%20Laena's%20husband%2C%20Daemon%2C%20is%20given%20that%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Laena%20takes%20her%20fate%20into%20her%20own%20hands%20and%20opts%20for%20a%20dragonrider's%20death.%20While%20still%20in%20labor%2C%20she%20orders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fall-targaryen-dragons-house-of-the-dragon-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eher%20dragon%2C%20Vhagar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20incinerate%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20book%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ELaena%20officially%20dies%20of%20%26quot%3Bchildbed%20fever%26quot%3B%20and%20apparently%20doesn't%20make%20it%20to%20Vhagar%20in%20time%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20her%20final%20hour%2C%20it%20is%20said%2C%20Lady%20Laena%20rose%20from%20her%20bed%2C%20pushed%20away%20the%20septas%20praying%20over%20her%2C%20and%20made%20her%20way%20from%20her%20room%2C%20intent%20on%20reaching%20Vhagar%20that%20she%20might%20fly%20one%20last%20time%20before%20she%20died.%20Her%20strength%20failed%20her%20on%20the%20tower%20steps%2C%20however%2C%20and%20it%20was%20there%20she%20collapsed%20and%20died.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELaenor%20fakes%20his%20own%20death%20in%20a%20big%20change%20from%20the%20book.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Arty%20Froushan%20and%20John%20MacMillan%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20season%20one%2C%20episode%20seven.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3c1852a25092c74cc9e58d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELaenor's%20death%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20ruse.%3Cp%3EOllie%20Upton%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20show%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Even%20after%20marrying%20and%20having%20children%20with%20other%20people%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-of-the-dragon-emma-darcy-slams-daemon-rhaenyra-grooming-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDaemon%20and%20Princess%20Rhaenyra%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Emma%20D'Arcy)%20are%20drawn%20to%20each%20other.%20They%20want%20to%20make%20it%20official%20as%20husband%20and%20wife%2C%20but%20Rhaenyra%20is%20trapped%20in%20a%20lavender%20marriage%20with%20Laenor%20(John%20MacMillan).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaemon%20and%20Rhaenyra%20seem%20to%20conspire%20to%20kill%20Laenor%20so%20they%20can%20finally%20be%20together%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20what%20Laenor's%20mother%20long%20believed%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20show%20reveals%20that%20Laenor%20was%20in%20cahoots%20with%20the%20couple%20all%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaemon%20kills%20a%20High%20Tide%20castle%20servant%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-of-the-dragon-laenor-qarl-change-fire-and-blood-deaths-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELaenor%20and%20his%20lover%2C%20Qarl%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stage%20a%20sword%20fight%20in%20the%20main%20hall.%20After%20another%20servant%20runs%20to%20get%20help%2C%20Daemon%20presumably%20helps%20Laenor%20dress%20the%20body%20of%20the%20dead%20servant%20in%20his%20own%20clothes%2C%20and%20they%20burn%20the%20servant's%20face%20beyond%20recognition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaenor%20and%20Qarl%20sneak%20away%20to%20Essos%20with%20Daemon's%20help%2C%20leaving%20the%20realm%20to%20gossip%20about%20the%20tragic%20and%20fishy%20death%20of%20Rhaenyra's%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20book%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EQarl%20stabs%20Laenor%20in%20broad%20daylight.%20Rumors%20spread%20that%20it%20was%20an%20act%20of%20passionate%20jealousy%2C%20or%20maybe%20a%20murder%20plot%2C%20but%20no%20damning%20evidence%20was%20ever%20collected%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BSer%20Laenor%20Velaryon%2C%20husband%20to%20the%20Princess%20Rhaenyra%20and%20the%20putative%20father%20of%20her%20children%2C%20was%20slain%20whilst%20attending%20a%20fair%20in%20Spicetown%2C%20stabbed%20to%20death%20by%20his%20friend%20and%20companion%20Ser%20Qarl%20Correy.%20The%20two%20men%20had%20been%20quarreling%20loudly%20before%20blades%20were%20drawn%2C%20merchants%20at%20the%20fair%20told%20Lord%20Velaryon%20when%20he%20came%20to%20collect%20his%20son's%20body.%20Correy%20had%20fled%20by%20then%2C%20wounding%20several%20men%20who%20tried%20to%20hinder%20him.%20Some%20claimed%20a%20ship%20had%20been%20waiting%20for%20him%20offshore.%20He%20was%20never%20seen%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIn%20the%20book%2C%20Otto%20Hightower%20is%20executed%20as%20a%20traitor.%20The%20show%20makes%20his%20death%20more%20climactic%20by%20having%20Rhaenyra%20swing%20the%20sword.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rhys%20Ifans%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c7805764df161125a05bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERhys%20Ifans%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20the%20Dragon.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EOllie%20Upton%20%2F%20HBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20show%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20he's%20unceremoniously%20removed%20as%20Hand%20of%20the%20King%20by%20his%20grandson%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-of-the-dragon-tom-glynn-carney-interview-aegon-season-2-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKing%20Aegon%20II%20Targaryen%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Tom%20Glynn-Carney)%2C%20viewers%20barely%20see%20Otto%20Hightower%20(Rhys%20Ifans)%20until%20his%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOtto%20tells%20his%20daughter%2C%20Alicent%2C%20that%20he's%20returning%20to%20House%20Hightower's%20seat%20in%20Oldtown%2C%20though%20she%20finds%20it%20odd%20that%20he%20doesn't%20answer%20any%20of%20her%20letters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoes-rhaenyra-become-queen-house-of-the-dragon-fire-blood-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERhaenyra's%20return%20to%20King's%20Landing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20discover%20that%20Otto%20never%20made%20it%20home.%20He%20was%20captured%20and%20imprisoned%20in%20the%20Red%20Keep's%20dungeon%20by%20none%20other%20than%20Larys%2C%20Aegon's%20master%20of%20whisperers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOtto%20is%20brought%20before%20Rhaenyra%2C%20and%20Daemon%20urges%20her%20to%20execute%20Aegon's%20former%20Hand%20as%20a%20traitor.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20wish%20to%20rule%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bshow%20them%20you%20do%20not%20waver.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20Rhaenyra%20was%20raised%20to%20be%20a%20lady%2C%20not%20a%20knight.%20She%20has%20never%20beheaded%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20let%20alone%20the%20father%20of%20her%20childhood%20best%20friend.%20She%20panics%20and%20misses%20Otto's%20neck%20on%20her%20first%20stroke%2C%20burying%20her%20sword%20in%20his%20shoulder%20blades.%20On%20her%20second%20stroke%2C%20Rhaenyra%20cuts%20off%20Otto's%20head%2C%20choking%20back%20sobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20the%20book%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20Rhaenyra%20takes%20the%20Iron%20Throne%20in%20%26quot%3BFire%20%26amp%3B%20Blood%2C%26quot%3B%20it's%20said%20that%20she%20set%20about%20%26quot%3Brewarding%20her%20friends%20and%20inflicting%20savage%20punishments%20on%20those%20who%20had%20s