ne%20had%20already%20found%20her%20another%20layer.%20Before%20I%20realized%20she%20needed%20bedding%20for%20kindergarten%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-american-preschool-china-raising-daughter-los-angeles-early-education-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elocal%20Chinese%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20attended%20while%20we%20were%20there%20%E2%80%94%20my%20mother%20had%20packed%20everything%20and%20set%20it%20by%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20before%20long%2C%20I%20started%20feeling%20strangely%20displaced%20as%20a%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20only%20ice%20cream%2C%26quot%3B%20my%20mother%20would%20say%20whenever%20I%20tried%20to%20explain%20to%20my%20daughter%20why%20she%20shouldn't%20eat%20too%20many%20sweets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20quiet%20playtime%2C%20my%20father%20often%20interrupted%20to%20offer%20a%20puzzle%20or%20fruit.%20At%20meals%2C%20my%20mother%20encouraged%20%26quot%3Bjust%20one%20more%20bite%2C%26quot%3B%20often%20feeding%20her%20herself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20my%20daughter%20argued%20with%20my%20niece%20over%20a%20toy%2C%20my%20mother%20quickly%20redirected%20her%20attention%20instead%20of%20letting%20her%20work%20through%20her%20emotions.%20It%20wasn't%20how%20I%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-parenting-middle-schoolers-taught-me-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elearned%20to%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20child%20in%20China%2C%20I%20never%20questioned%20those%20habits.%20My%20grandparents%20raised%20me%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiving-up-american-dream-life-abroad-moving-to-asia-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELiving%20in%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%20changed%20how%20I%20think%20about%20parenting.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20carefully%20established%20routines%20around%20sleep%2C%20meals%2C%20screen%20time%2C%20and%20the%20boundaries%20we%20wanted%20to%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20China%2C%20those%20routines%20gradually%20disappeared.%20My%20family%20cared%20for%20my%20daughter%20with%20love%2C%20but%20their%20way%20of%20helping%20often%20left%20me%20feeling%20as%20though%20my%20role%20as%20her%20mother%20had%20quietly%20slipped%20into%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ea20e811-8402-4aa5-8038-3b9b905fc7e3%5C%22%3EMy%20daughter%20enjoyed%20the%20attention%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20seemed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-living-in-china-hard-to-relate-friends-back-home-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehappier%20than%20ever%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20family%20gatherings%2C%20she%20bounced%20from%20lap%20to%20lap%2C%20proudly%20shouted%20%26quot%3BXin%20Nian%20Kuai%20Le%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3BHappy%20New%20Year%26quot%3B)%20to%20relatives%2C%20and%20ate%20more%20than%20usual%20while%20competing%20with%20her%20cousin%20at%20mealtimes.%20Watching%20her%2C%20I%20felt%20both%20overwhelmed%20and%20deeply%20comforted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20the%20US%2C%20life%20quickly%20returned%20to%20normal.%20Once%20again%2C%20it%20was%20just%20my%20husband%20and%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20of%20three%20sitting%20on%20the%20grass%20in%20California.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3de162e218c3b62535d67d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223088%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShe%20says%20her%20daughter%20quickly%20adapted%20to%20life%20in%20America%20after%20returning%20from%20the%20trip.%3Cp%3EProvided%20by%20Grace%20Cong%20Sui%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20evening%2C%20I%20placed%20dinner%20in%20front%20of%20her%20as%20usual.%20Instead%20of%20reaching%20for%20her%20spoon%2C%20she%20sat%20quietly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMommy%2C%20feed%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20pointed%20to%20her%20utensils.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20do%20it%20yourself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20more%20firmly.%20%26quot%3BPlease%20feed%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20thinking%2C%20I%20picked%20up%20my%20spoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20fed%20her%2C%20I%20caught%20myself%20doing%20the%20very%20thing%20I'd%20spent%20weeks%20resisting%20in%20China.%20Part%20of%20it%20was%20exhaustion.%20Part%20of%20it%20was%20the%20familiar%20worry%20that%20she%20wouldn't%20eat%20enough%20if%20I%20didn't%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20moment%2C%20I%20realized%20how%20easily%20old%20habits%20can%20resurface.%20I%20had%20thought%20I'd%20left%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-style-only-teach-children-when-interested-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estyle%20of%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E%20behind%2C%20but%20it%20was%20still%20part%20of%20me%2C%20shaped%20by%20the%20family%20who%20had%20raised%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20still%20asks%20when%20we%20can%20go%20back%20to%20China%20to%20see%20her%20grandparents.%20She%20misses%20the%20constant%20attention%20and%20the%20feeling%20of%20being%20surrounded%20by%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20believe%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20should%20make%20the%20decisions%20about%20how%20we%20raise%20her.%20But%20I%20no%20longer%20see%20my%20parents'%20approach%20as%20simply%20something%20to%20resist.%20It%20came%20from%20love%2C%20just%20as%20mine%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20I'm%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20parts%20of%20each%20I%20want%20to%20pass%20on%20to%20my%20daughter%20as%20we%20navigate%20motherhood%20%E2%80%94%20and%20childhood%20%E2%80%94%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-american-travel-to-china-spend-time-family-parenting-style-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782692041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2