ton.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20work%20as%20a%20marketing%20coordinator%20at%20a%20local%20hospital%20in%20Houston.%20I%20worked%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-work-from-home-jobs-persisting-fewer-new-roles-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehybrid%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20spending%20three%20days%20working%20from%20home%20and%20two%20days%20in%20the%20office%2C%20earning%20about%20%2470%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20and%20I%20enjoyed%20it.%20That's%20until%20I%20got%20pregnant%20with%20my%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20so%20happy%3B%C2%A0my%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20been%20trying%20to%20get%20pregnant%20for%20months.%20I%20didn't%20really%20think%20about%20what%20would%20happen%20once%20he%20was%20born%2C%20as%20I%20just%20thought%20I'd%20go%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20day%20before%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-took-5-maternity-leaves-teacher-benefits-policies-ohio-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ematernity%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20ended%2C%20my%20boss%20called%20me%20and%20said%20he%20was%20taking%20away%20my%20flexibility%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%20and%20he%20wanted%20me%20in%20the%20office%2040%20hours%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20a%20state%20of%20shock%2C%20but%20the%20choice%20was%20clear.%20I%20handed%20in%20my%20resignation%20letter%20almost%20immediately%20and%20became%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226b103c14-a88e-4cf2-8afd-ea92602335dc%5C%22%3EWorking%20on%204%20side%20hustles%20at%20once%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20living%20on%20one%20income%20from%202023%20to%20the%20beginning%20of%202026%2C%20during%20which%20we%20had%20our%20second%20child%2C%20a%20girl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20gave%20up%20my%20salary%2C%20half%20of%20my%20husband's%20take-home%20pay%20went%20toward%20our%20mortgage%2C%20so%20the%20money%20was%20starting%20to%20feel%20a%20little%20tight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20wishing%20I%20could%20bring%20in%20an%20extra%20couple%20of%20hundred%20dollars%20a%20month%20to%20help%20us%20cover%20our%20groceries.%20I%20saw%20all%20these%20women%20online%20making%20money%20through%20content%20creation%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-side-hustle-creativity-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eside%20hustles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20inspired%20me%20to%20try%20it%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20you%20a%20side%20hustler%3F%20Do%20you%20use%20AI%20to%20help%20manage%20multiple%20workflows%3F%20Have%20you%20turned%20your%20side%20gig%20into%20your%20main%20job%3F%20We%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Fill%20out%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSe-HAYcstsp8DaAZe2AgYMwKD9MwwFwn9ebRPHOlIYhEXLhzQ%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Ddialog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshort%20form%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20share%20your%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20in%20January%2C%20I%20made%20a%20video%20on%20Instagram%20sharing%20how%20much%20debt%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20in%20total%20and%20how%20much%20I%20planned%20to%20pay%20off%20this%20year%2C%20which%20was%20%2418%2C000.%20This%20was%20everything%20except%20our%20mortgage%2C%20including%20our%20student%20loans%2C%20medical%20debt%20from%20having%20our%20kids%2C%20and%20some%20credit%20card%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20six%20months%2C%20I've%20dabbled%20in%20mystery%20shopping%2C%20creating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuser-generated-content-creator-make-thousands-per-month-social-media-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euser-generated%20content%3C%2Fa%3E%20(UGC)%20for%20brands%20on%20social%20media%2C%20doing%20brand%20deals%2C%20and%20freelance%20graphic%20design%20work.%20I've%20also%20experimented%20with%20print-on-demand%20products%20sold%20through%20Etsy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUGC%20takes%20up%20most%20of%20my%20time%2C%20about%2010%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20which%20involves%20scripting%2C%20filming%2C%20and%20editing%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20my%20earnings%20from%20side%20gigs%20have%20helped%20me%20reduce%20our%20debt%20from%20%2418%2C000%20to%20%2413%2C100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229edac9f3-b152-4e87-b456-3cc2434a3507%5C%22%3EBalancing%20side%20gigs%20and%20motherhood%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20day%2C%20I%20work%20while%20my%20son%20and%20daughter%20nap.%20When%20they're%20both%20asleep%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20usually%20have%20an%20hour%20or%20two%20during%20the%20day%20when%20I%20can%20work.%20That's%20really%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20from%20about%207%20p.m.%20to%20midnight%2C%20I%20have%20time%20to%20do%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstay-at-home-mom-making-1500-weekly-from-side-hustles-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euninterrupted%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20my%20husband%20comes%20home%2C%20looks%20after%20the%20kids%2C%20and%20handles%20their%20bedtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20side%20hustles%20have%20affected%20the%20time%20I%20spend%20with%20my%20husband.%20It's%20either%20work%20or%20time%20with%20the%20kids%2C%20because%20we%20don't%20have%20house%20help.%20I'm%20thinking%20about%20having%20at%20least%20one%20day%20a%20week%20when%20I%20don't%20use%20social%20media%20at%20all%20so%20that%20I%20can%20focus%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-work-together-keep-marriage-strong-maintain-relationship-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emy%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20love%20about%20working%20side%20gigs%20is%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20answer%20to%20anyone%2C%20unlike%20in%20my%20previous%20job.%20If%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20a%20day%20off%20because%20my%20kids%20are%20sick%20or%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20my%20kids%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20ask%20anybody.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229a9b1791-b3d0-425b-9257-c9a7c294f3a2%5C%22%3EFeeling%20like%20myself%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20had%20my%20kids%2C%20I%20gave%20all%20of%20myself%20and%20my%20energy%20to%20them%20and%20lost%20myself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-career-stay-at-home-mom-guilt-identity-money-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ein%20motherhood%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'd%20realize%20that%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20I%20didn't%20really%20do%20anything%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20didn't%20love%20giving%20up%20my%20salary%20and%20living%20off%20one%20income.%20I%20understand%20we're%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarried-couple-separate-finances-personal-experience-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emarried%20couple%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20it's%20our%20money%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20bring%20in%20my%20own%20money%20so%20I%20could%20buy%20things%20for%20myself%2C%20and%20not%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20my%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20budget%20hard%2C%20so%20every%20dollar%20has%20a%20job.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20month%2C%20all%20the%20money%20is%20automatically%20assigned%20to%20something%2C%20like%20the%20mortgage%2C%20bills%2C%20groceries%2C%20or%20diapers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20not%20much%20left%20over%2C%20and%20if%20we%20spend%20money%20on%20something%20for%20me%2C%20I%20start%20to%20feel%20really%20guilty.%20So%20I%20think%20the%20biggest%20achievement%20for%20me%20is%20that%20I%20can%20bring%20in%20some%20money%2C%20for%20myself%20and%20for%20my%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContent%20creation%20has%20been%20such%20a%20creative%20outlet%20for%20me%2C%20and%20I've%20always%20been%20a%20creative%20person%2C%20so%20it%20feels%20like%20my%20skills%20aren't%20going%20to%20waste.%20It's%20given%20me%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20my%20spark%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cd