2C%20she%20also%20pays%20attention%20to%20my%20preferences%2C%20which%20makes%20me%20feel%20seen%20and%20cared%20for.%20She's%20not%20just%20saying%20%26quot%3BI'm%20taking%20care%20of%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20me%2C%20she's%20also%20saying%20%26quot%3BI'm%20interested%20in%20who%20you%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author's%20partner's%20mom%20prepares%20food%20for%20a%20family%20meal.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3d4916a25092c74cc9f2b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20she%20was%20nervous%20about%20how%20she%20and%20her%20partner's%20mom%20would%20connect%20in%20a%20meaningful%20way%20since%20they%20don't%20share%20a%20language.%20Food%20became%20the%20solution.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Catherine%20Work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2219d16a8c-26aa-43d0-958f-77498fa5f79c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20relationship%20with%20food%20was%20different%20growing%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20I%20hated%20onions.%20Every%20time%20my%20mom%20made%20pasta%2C%20she'd%20add%20lots%20of%20onions%20to%20the%20jarred%20tomato%20sauce.%20I%20recall%20asking%20her%20if%2C%20just%20once%2C%20she%20could%20add%20the%20onions%20in%20after%20I%20had%20served%20myself%2C%20but%20there%20on%20my%20dinner%20plate%2C%20was%20always%20onions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20continued%20when%20I%20was%20older.%20I%20always%20felt%20like%20she%20didn't%20know%20the%20types%20of%20food%20I%20liked%20or%20ate.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20only%20started%20liking%20mushrooms%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20when%20I'd%20visit%20her%2C%20she%20told%20me%20I%20loved%20mushrooms.%20One%20year%2C%20on%20my%20birthday%2C%20she%20brought%20out%20a%20chocolate%20cake%20and%20told%20everyone%20it%20was%20my%20favorite.%20It's%20not%2C%20I%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbronx-bakery-beloved-carrot-cake-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecarrot%20cake%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b14ef8a-7437-4d08-87dd-bfb6a912b0b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20boyfriend's%20mom%20started%20paying%20attention%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20boyfriend's%20mom%20started%20asking%20if%20I%20liked%20the%20dishes%20she%20cooked.%20She%20wanted%20to%20know%20which%20ones%20I%20enjoyed%2C%20what%20was%20too%20spicy%2C%20and%20what%20flavors%20I%20liked%20best.%20Looking%20back%2C%20I%20can%20tell%20that%20she%20was%20gathering%20data%20and%20taking%20notes%20in%20her%20head.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20garden%20view%20showing%20dill%20and%20cilantro.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3d48b6a25092c74cc9f2ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20her%20partner's%20mother%20doesn't%20care%20for%20dill%20or%20cilantro%2C%20but%20she%20still%20planted%20some%20in%20her%20garden%20for%20when%20they%20visit.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Catherine%20Work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20when%20her%20son%20and%20I%20come%20to%20visit%2C%20she%20has%20the%20fridge%20stocked%20with%20foods%20we%20both%20like.%20She%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcilantro-corriander-taste-gene-found-2012-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eplanted%20dill%20and%20cilantro%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20her%20garden%20(even%20though%20she%20doesn't%20eat%20them).%20She%20knows%20I%20like%20my%20food%20saltier.%20She%20keeps%20a%20bottle%20of%20balsamic%20vinegar%20under%20the%20sink%20even%20though%20nobody%20else%20uses%20it%2C%20and%20she%20keeps%20my%20preferred%20spices%20and%20teas%20in%20her%20cupboard%20for%20when%20I%20visit.%20If%20my%20boyfriend%20and%20I%20miss%20a%20holiday%20with%20her%2C%20she%20puts%20some%20of%20our%20favorite%20foods%20in%20the%20freezer%20for%20when%20we%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b001396e-dd98-4d55-b5aa-892ce27d46e5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20noticed%20we%20had%20become%20vegetarians%20before%20we%20told%20anyone%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20clicked%20last%20year%20when%20she%20told%20my%20partner%20and%20me%20that%20she%20had%20noticed%20we%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feating-vegetarian-diet-for-50-years-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estopped%20eating%20meat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20so%20for%20an%20upcoming%20event%2C%20she%20had%20requested%20vegetarian%20options%20for%20us.%20We%20hadn't%20told%20anyone%20about%20our%20lifestyle%20change%2C%20but%20she%20knew.%20She%20had%20been%20paying%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20when%20I%20became%20a%20vegetarian%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20my%20early%2020s%2C%20I%20faced%20a%20lot%20of%20pushback%20from%20my%20parents.%20My%20mom%20stocked%20the%20fridge%20with%20lots%20of%20beef%20and%20offered%20to%20cook%20me%20chicken.%20When%20I%20became%20a%20vegetarian%20a%20year%20ago%20at%2031%2C%20it%20was%20easier%20because%20I%20had%20more%20support%20this%20time%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20my%20boyfriend's%20mom%20has%20tried%20her%20hand%20at%20making%20vegetarian%20versions%20of%20classic%20Italian%20dishes%2C%20and%20she%20keeps%20the%20freezer%20stocked%20full%20of%20beans%20for%20when%20she%20cooks%20meat%20for%20others%20at%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fresh%20pasta%20on%20a%20wood%20cutting%20board%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3d489da25092c74cc9f2ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20that%20her%20partner's%20mom%20pays%20close%20attention%20to%20food%20preferences%20and%20even%20noticed%20that%20she%20and%20her%20boyfriend%20had%20become%20vegetarians%20before%20they%20told%20her.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Catherine%20Work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0d754fe-195d-45d1-8553-8ff1ef6cfc8a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFood%20became%20our%20shared%20language%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20like%20to%20think%20I'm%20special%2C%20but%20I%20know%20my%20partner's%20mother%20has%20a%20mental%20notebook%20of%20what%20everyone%20in%20the%20family%20likes%20to%20eat%20(and%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20boyfriend's%20family%20shares%20the%20same%20talent).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20saves%20cookies%20for%20people%2C%20she%20knows%20who%20likes%20lemon%20on%20their%20food%20and%20who%20doesn't%2C%20and%20what%20each%20of%20us%20will%20want%20on%20our%20pizza.%20In%20the%20four%20years%20I've%20known%20my%20boyfriend's%20mom%2C%20I've%20learned%20enough%20Italian%20to%20communicate%3A%20to%20thank%20her%2C%20to%20tell%20her%20I'm%20happy%20around%20her%2C%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20bake%20with%20her%2C%20and%20to%20ask%20her%20what%20food%20she%20likes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20words%20aren't%20enough%20(and%20when%20my%20attempt%20at%20Italian%20sounds%20very%20broken)%2C%20we%20can%20eat%20together.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flanguage-barrier-dont-speak-same-language-inlaw-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782658622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a32e4d32bbd1d834ef24ff4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flanguage-barrier-dont-speak-same-language-inlaw-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Food%20has%20become%20the%20way%20my%20partner's%20mother%20communicates%20and%20shows%20her%20love%20for%20me.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Work)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Indian%20H1-B%20holders%20are%E2%80%A6%E2%80%99%3A%20Immigration%20lawyer%20says%20waiting%20on%20green%20cards%20