s.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fuae-condemns-iranian-attacks-on-bahrain-kuwait-reiterates-full-solidarity-with-gulf-neighbours%2Famp_articleshow%2F132050379.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20worked%20in%20restaurants%20for%2035%20years.%20There's%20one%20food%20I%20avoid%20ordering%20on%20Mondays.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223468%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Brian%20Russino%20in%20a%20kitchen%20setting.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3ed667360acd489560c20f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221951%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBrian%20Russino%20is%20a%2035-year%20restaurant%20vet%20and%20kitchen%20operations%20manager%20for%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20personal%20rule%20of%20thumb%20he%20follows%20is%20to%20avoid%20the%20%26quot%3BMonday%20bun.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%20prevents%20the%20%26quot%3BMonday%20bun%26quot%3B%20with%20strict%20systems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Brian%20%26quot%3BRusty%26quot%3B%20Russino%2C%20an%20area%20kitchen%20operations%20manager%20for%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory.%20He%20oversees%20nine%20busy%20Southern%20California%20restaurants%20across%20Orange%20County%20and%20San%20Diego.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20spent%20more%20than%2035%20years%20in%20the%20restaurant%20industry%20and%20more%20than%2022%20years%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheesecake-factory-food-made-in-house-except-cheesecake-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20Cheesecake%20Factory%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I've%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20food%20quality%2C%20inventory%20management%2C%20and%20how%20restaurants%20handle%20fresh%20ingredients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20there's%20one%20habit%20I've%20developed%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-cheesecake-factory-history-timeline-photos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edining%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20still%20influences%20what%20I%20order%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20call%20it%20the%20%26quot%3BMonday%20bun.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227008%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Basket%20of%20bread%20buns.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3ed710a25092c74cca009b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMonday%20buns%20may%20not%20be%20as%20fresh%20as%20they%20can%20be.%3Cp%3EThai%20Liang%20Lim%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20something%20I%20used%20to%20joke%20about%20with%20my%20wife%20when%20we%20went%20out%20to%20eat%20on%20Mondays%20and%20Tuesdays%2C%20which%20were%20often%20my%20days%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20clear%2C%20the%20Monday%20bun%20isn't%20about%20food%20safety.%20It's%20about%20freshness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20personal%20rule%20of%20thumb%20I've%20developed%20over%20the%20years%20when%20eating%20at%20restaurants%20in%20general%E2%80%94not%20something%20I%20associate%20with%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b0e3648e-2192-46c2-a223-cef674a1c403%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20I%20avoid%20buns%20on%20Mondays%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20profession%2C%20I've%20noticed%20that%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-cheesecake-factory-runs-one-of-americas-biggest-menus-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erestaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%20receive%20deliveries%20on%20Fridays%20or%20Saturdays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223468%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Brian%20Russino%20in%20a%20kitchen%20setting.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3ed667360acd489560c20f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221951%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrian%20Russino%20oversees%20nine%20Southern%20California%20Cheesecake%20Factory%20restaurants%20across%20Orange%20County%20and%20San%20Diego.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20don't%20use%20all%20of%20that%20product%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20some%20of%20it%20may%20still%20be%20in%20inventory%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20anything%20is%20wrong%20with%20it.%20It%20simply%20means%20that%20it's%20not%20as%20fresh%20as%20it%20could%20be.%20Bread%20is%20a%20prime%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bun%20that's%20been%20around%20for%20a%20few%20days%20can%20be%20very%20different%20from%20one%20that%20arrived%20more%20recently.%20It%20may%20not%20be%20as%20soft%20and%20pillowy%20as%20I'd%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3BMonday%20bun%26quot%3B%20came%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20example%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-seafood-restaurant-in-every-state-according-to-yelp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eseafood%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Again%2C%20I'm%20not%20saying%20it's%20unsafe.%20I'm%20saying%20it%20may%20not%20be%20as%20fresh%20as%20it%20was%20a%20few%20days%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ffa36943-044f-432e-9806-1e2d5e593aab%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20systems%20I%20rely%20on%20in%20restaurants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brian%20Russino%20in%20cook%20uniform%20standing%20next%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Cheesecake%20Factory%26quot%3B%20sign.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3ed795360acd489560c226%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussino%20says%20that%20he%20and%20his%20colleagues%20take%20pride%20at%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%20in%20ensuring%20guests%20don't%20experience%20the%20%26quot%3BMonday%20Bun.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20I%20have%20confidence%20when%20dining%20out%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwolfgang-pucks-daily-routine-rules-build-lasting-restaurant-empire-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20restaurants%20have%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20place%20to%20manage%20freshness%20and%20food%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%2C%20for%20example%2C%20we%20date%20products%20upon%20arrival%2C%20follow%20rotation%20systems%2C%20and%20track%20shelf%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheesecake-factory-vp-shares-3-questions-always-asked-get-ahead-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epeople%20responsible%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20validating%20products%20as%20they%20come%20through%20the%20back%20door%2C%20and%20we%20pay%20close%20attention%20to%20how%20ingredients%20are%20stored%20and%20cared%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20use%20forecasting%20and%20ordering%20systems%20designed%20to%20help%20us%20avoid%20carrying%20excess%20inventory.%20We're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-family-owned-brooklyn-bakery-50-years-of-tradition-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebusy%20restaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that's%20one%20reason%20we%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20product%20sitting%20around%20after%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20after%2035%20years%20in%20restaurants%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BMonday%20bun%26quot%3B%20has%20stuck%20with%20me%20as%20a%20personal%20habit%20when%20I'm%20dining%20out.%20It's%20simply%20one%20of%20those%20industry%20quirks%20that%20makes%20me%20think%20about%20freshness%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20week.%20But%20thanks%20to%20the%20inventory%20and%20quality%20systems%20we%20use%20at%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%2C%20it's%20not%20something%20I%20worry%20about%20in%20our%20own%20restaurants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-restaurants-35-years-1-food-avoid-ordering-on-mondays-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782647821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3ed676a25092c74cca0092%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-restaurants-35-years-1-food-avoid-ordering-on-mondays-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brian%20%26quot%3BRusty%26quot%3B%20Russino%20of%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%20shares%20restaurant%20insights%2C%20explaining%20his%20%26quot%3BMonday%20bun%26quot%3B%20rule%20for%20ordering%20fresh%20food.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jorwig%40businessinsider.com%20(Jessica%20Orwig)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20took%20an%20unpaid%20internship%20at%2031.%20I%20learned%20more%20valuable%20lessons%20from%20my%20Gen%20Z%20fellow%20interns%20than%20from%20my%20bosses.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20group%20of%20gen%20z%20coworkers%20in%20an%20office%20conference%20room%20looking%20at%20post%20its%20on%20the%20window%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3e9dd0e218c3b62535da5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(not%20pictured)%20was%20the%20oldest%20intern%20in%20the%20office.%3Cp%3ELeoPatrizi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAt%2031%2C%20I%20quit%20my%20job%20and%20became%20an%20intern%3B%20the%20other%20interns%20were%20Gen%20Z%20and%20a%20full%20decade%20younger.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Gen%20Z%20interns%20taught%20me%20valuable%20lessons%2C%20like%20the%20power%20of%20asking%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%20and%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%20that%20I'm%20in%20my%20dream%20career%2C%20I%20still%20use%20those%20lessons%20in%20my%20work%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-pivot-unpaid-intern-dream-job-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equit%20my%20full%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20role%20to%20take%20an%20unpaid%20internship%20that%20eventually%20earned%20me%20my%20dream%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20so%20much%20from%20the%20opportunity%20to%20start%20from%20scratch%2C%20yet%20my%20most%20useful%20lessons%20came%20not%20from%20management%2C%20but%20from%20my%20fellow%20interns%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20whom%20were%20a%20decade%20younger%20than%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeadlines%20often%20paint%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-managers-employees-most-challenging-technological-skills-survey-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20being%20the%20most%20challenging%20generation%20to%20work%20with.%20But%20that%20wasn't%20my%20experience%20at%20all.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20found%20them%20to%20be%20perfectly%20practical%20and%20rather%20inspirational.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20alongside%20them%20as%20a%2031-year-old%20with%20nearly%20a%20decade%20of%20experience%20made%20me%20wonder%20whether%20some%20of%20what%20gets%20criticized%20as%20weakness%20is%20actually%20a%20paradigm%20shift%20toward%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Femotional-intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemotional%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20two%20lessons%20my%20fellow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-grads-better-prepared-ai-workforce-cant-get-jobs-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20interns%3C%2Fa%3E%20taught%20me%20that%20made%20me%20question%20which%20aspects%20of%20professionalism%20I'd%20learned%20were%20wisdom%20and%20which%20were%20toxic%20work-culture%20conditioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ffd74637-0c05-486e-947c-7263fb76d9ba%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsk%20the%20big%20questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20day%20one%2C%20I%20noticed%20their%20willingness%20to%20ask%20The%20Big%20Questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMakes%20sense%2C%20right%3F%20Interns%20are%20supposed%20to%20ask%20questions.%20But%20while%20all%20of%20us%20asked%20the%20usual%20procedural%20questions%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20the%20youngest%20in%20our%20crowd%20were%20always%20ready%20to%20skip%20superficialities%20and%20go%20straight%20for%20the%20jugular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%3F%26quot%3B%20they%20asked%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20genuinely%20wanted%20to%20know%20and%20offer%20their%20two%20cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20are%20we%20doing%20it%20like%20this%3F%20Why%20is%20this%20the%20process%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20particular%20procedure%20came%20off%20as%20convoluted%20or%20confusing%2C%20they%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EWhy%20do%20it%20this%20way%20when%20we%20could%20just%20do%20it%20that%20way%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20When%20a%20procedure%20came%20off%20as%20redundant%20or%20lacking%20in%20value%2C%20they%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3B...%3Cem%3Ewhy%20bother%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20in%20professional%20settings%20for%20years%2C%20I%20was%20used%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fso-many-executives-in-the-corporate-c-suite-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupper%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20closed%20to%20conversations%20that%20go%20beyond%20doling%20out%20instructions.%20I%20realized%20I%20hadn't%20asked%20a%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%20question%20beyond%20the%20interview%20stage%20in%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20reminded%20me%20that%20questions%20are%20tiny%20signals%20that%20convey%3A%20while%20we%20trust%20our%20team%20to%20guide%20us%2C%20business%20as%20usual%20may%20not%20be%20the%20only%20path%20to%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuestioning%20helps%20keep%20the%20core%20philosophy%20behind%20what%20we%20do%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20our%20minds%2C%20so%20we%20can%20operate%20more%20effectively%20and%20be%20more%20aligned%20with%20our%20overall%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d447e746-c93b-4ee5-850a-5a77595752b6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EProtect%20time%20with%20boundaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20internship%20workload%20increased%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20my%20fellow%20Gen%20Z%20interns%20fiercely%20protected%20their%20time.%20They%20cared%20about%20their%20work%20and%20worked%20hard%2C%20but%20when%20the%20clock%20ticked%205%20p.m.%2C%20they%20were%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20took%20their%20work%20hours%20literally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20when%20I%20got%20my%20first%20job%2C%20a%20Xillennial%20coworker%20told%20me%20to%20say%20goodbye%20to%20my%20free%20time.%20Several%20people%20in%20the%20company%20had%20the%20same%20mantra%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-to-work-weekends-career-benefits-schedule-advantages-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20on%20weekends%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20price%20of%20a%20promotion%20someday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interns%20I%20personally%20connected%20with%3F%20Well%2C%20I%20learned%20quickly%20that%20when%20they%20were%20out%2C%20they%20were%20out%20and%20gone.%20They%20were%20balancing%20school%2C%20personal%20obligations%2C%20the%20internship%20itself%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-home-after-college-no-social-life-lonely-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20knew%20how%20to%20block%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20set%20boundaries.%20They%20had%20lunch%2C%20clocked%20out%20on%20time%2C%20and%20communicated%20when%20they%20needed%20a%20brain%20break.%20No%2C%20they%20weren't%20lazy%3B%20they%20simply%20embodied%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20I%20was%20juggling%20nine%20different%20freelance%20roles%2C%20building%20a%20small%20business%20on%20the%20side%2C%20and%20still%20tediously%20rearranging%20my%20bare-minimum%20sleep%20schedule%20so%20that%2C%20if%20I%20needed%20to%20stay%20late%2C%20I%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20reminded%20me%20that%20constant%20availability%20is%20not%20proof%20of%20dedication.%20Answering%20an%20email%20in%20thirty%20seconds%20is%20nice%2C%20but%20not%20an%20indicator%20of%20commitment.%20Taking%20on%20extra%20work%20that%20carried%20beyond%20hours%20just%20to%20say%20%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20was%20not%20a%20strength%2C%20especially%20if%20it%20came%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225078f043-3c58-4bc5-9cf3-54990330b8da%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20skills%20behind%20the%20lessons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20takeaway%20isn't%20that%20Gen%20Z%20has%20everything%20figured%20out.%20None%20of%20us%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20takeaway%20is%20that%20Gen%20Z%20taught%20me%20an%20invaluable%20lesson%3A%20curiosity%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20big%20questions%2C%20and%20self-respect%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20boundary-setting%2C%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskills-all-students-need-succeed-global-teacher-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eessential%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsking%20questions%20creates%20understanding%2C%20and%20boundaries%20create%20sustainability.%20Together%2C%20they%20create%20a%20work%20environment%20with%20clarity%2C%20respect%2C%20and%20high%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20know%20these%20skills%20can%20be%20stunted%20once%20we%20begin%20ascending%20into%20large-company%20roles%20because%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20internship%2C%20my%20fellow%20interns%20taught%20me%20one%20last%20critical%20lesson%3A%20I%20%3Cem%3Eused%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20have%20these%20same%20skills%20once%20upon%20a%20time.%20But%20I'd%20unlearned%20them%20over%20the%20years%2C%20thinking%20the