3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20board%3C%2Fa%3E%20alerts%20in%20the%20morning%20for%20jobs%20that%20match%20your%20requirements.%20I%20like%20niche%20job%20boards%20and%20even%20Google%2C%20which%20searches%20across%20all%20job%20boards.%20Once%20you%20start%20your%20search%2C%20if%20there%20are%20companies%20you%20really%20want%20to%20work%20for%2C%20bookmark%20their%20personal%20job%20boards%20so%20you%20can%20easily%20check%20them%20each%20day%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20checking%20your%20alerts%2C%20you%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-job-search-white-collar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eapply%20to%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20no%20jobs%20interest%20you%20that%20day%2C%20even%20better.%20That%20gives%20you%20an%20excuse%20to%20take%20more%20time%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20people%20say%20they%20just%20want%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20job%20to%20feel%20like%20they've%20done%20something%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20like%20that's%20a%20waste%20of%20time.%20If%20no%20jobs%20are%20speaking%20to%20you%2C%20I'd%20rather%20have%20you%20spend%20that%20time%20on%20other%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222475f22b-461f-4640-b1b8-c46a9f5c00cd%5C%22%3EDedicate%2030%20minutes%20to%20an%20hour%20each%20day%20to%20commenting%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20finding%20that%20recruiters%20are%20so%20overwhelmed%20with%20applicants%20that%20they're%20going%20back%20to%20old-school%20sourcing%20and%20finding%20people%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20advice%20is%20to%20search%20for%20topics%20on%20LinkedIn%20that%20interest%20you%20and%20are%20in%20your%20industry.%20If%20you're%20in%20consumer%20goods%2C%20type%20%26quot%3Bconsumer%20goods%26quot%3B%20into%20the%20search%20bar.%20Find%20people%20who%20are%20writing%20about%20it%20and%20leave%20a%20thoughtful%20comment%20on%20their%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22475a9c05-f6cc-4195-8de5-f4483863ec2b%5C%22%3ETake%20a%20leisurely%20break%20around%20lunchtime%20and%20then%20network%20for%201%20to%202%20hours%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20really%20productive%20morning%2C%20get%20some%20food%20in%2C%20move%20your%20body%2C%20play%20with%20your%20animals%2C%20and%20do%20whatever%20makes%20you%20feel%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20an%20athlete%20training%20for%20a%20marathon%2C%20you'd%20have%20rest%20days%20and%20take%20breaks.%20Job%20seekers%20have%20to%20do%20the%20same%20thing.%20You'll%20reenergize%20to%20get%20through%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20afternoon%2C%20which%20should%20consist%20of%20at%20least%20one%20to%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-not-to-do-networking-mistakes-etiquette-expert-tips-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehours%20of%20networking%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHands%20down%2C%20networking%20is%20my%20favorite%20way%20to%20find%20a%20job.%20I%20find%20that%20many%20job%20seekers%20don't%20like%20it%2C%20but%20it's%20just%20as%20important%20as%20applying%20to%20jobs.%20Your%20afternoon%20of%20networking%20could%20look%20like%20researching%20people%20to%20contact%2C%20sending%20out%20messages%2C%20going%20for%20coffee%20chats%2C%20or%20reaching%20out%20to%20old%20coworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22806936cc-1004-4e57-8b6a-431360aa353a%5C%22%3EClose%20the%20computer%20and%20walk%20away%20without%20guilt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20job%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day%20is%20to%20engage%20in%20activities%20that%20fill%20your%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-looking-for-work-you-should-volunteer-job-recruiter-says-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efound%20volunteering%20to%20be%20amazing%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20my%20clients%20because%20it%20gives%20them%20a%20sense%20of%20community%2C%20helps%20them%20meet%20like-minded%2C%20generous%20people%2C%20and%20makes%20them%20feel%20productive.%20So%20I%20say%20volunteer%2C%20exercise%2C%20meet%20friends%2C%20work%20on%20your%20hobby%2C%20cook%20your%20favorite%20dinner%2C%20jam%20out%20to%20your%20favorite%20songs%2C%20or%20play%20guitar%20for%20three%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20day%20is%20going%20to%20fluctuate%20depending%20on%20whether%20you%20see%20more%20jobs%20you%20like%20or%20if%20you%20have%20some%20more%20networking%20to%20do%2C%20but%20that%20shouldn't%20take%20eight%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2285f4080b-e85d-412e-89bb-eb838be7045c%5C%22%3EMore%20is%20not%20always%20better%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20job%20alert%20comes%20in%20the%20afternoon%20for%20something%20that%20really%20excites%20you%2C%20go%20jump%20on%20that%2C%20but%20remember%20that%20doing%20more%20is%20not%20always%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20get%20why%20people%20feel%20they%20should%20push%20through%20on%20applications%20for%20jobs%20they%20don't%20even%20really%20want.%20If%20you're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F50-unemployed-worried-hiring-managers-see-desperation-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworried%20about%20paying%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20everyone's%20breathing%20down%20your%20neck%2C%20you%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BLook%2C%20I%20applied%20to%2010%20jobs%20today.%20I'm%20doing%20what%20I%20can.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20I%20really%20don't%20like%20the%20word%20should%3A%20it%20implies%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20doing%20the%20same%20thing%20over%20and%20over%20and%20not%20getting%20the%20results%20that%20you%20want%2C%20switch%20up%20the%20tactic.%20Give%20yourself%20permission%20to%20take%20a%20break%20and%20refill%20your%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20navigating%20the%20job%20market%3F%20If%20so%2C%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporter%20at%20tmartinelli%40businessinsider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-recommends-four-hour-burnout-proof-job